<%# landing-page: standalone marketing / SEO page (app/views/public), not part of a user's blog %>
<%= content_for :title do %>
  Substack alternative without the 10% revenue share — Pagecord
<% end %>

<%= content_for :og_image do %>
  <%= dynamic_og_image_for_landing_page(title: "A Better Substack Alternative") %>
<% end %>

<%= content_for :meta_description do %>
  A Substack alternative for personal sites, not publications. No revenue share, no $50 custom domain fee, and a free plan for the blogging basics.
<% end %>

<div class="md:mt-4 mb-4 md:mb-8 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4">
  <h1 class="source-serif font-semibold text-center text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">
    Substack is for publications. Pagecord is for personal sites.
  </h1>

  <div class="md:text-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 flex flex-col gap-y-4">
    <p class="mt-8 md:mt-12">
      Substack is a great fit if you want to run a publication and monetise your blog. Many people want something different: a small home on the web that can also send posts by email.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pagecord gives you a blog first: posts, pages, RSS, themes, a custom domain, and export. Email subscribers are there when you want them, with per-post delivery or a weekly digest, but the site is still yours even if you never become a newsletter operator.
    </p>
    <p>
      No revenue share. No $50 custom domain fee. Open source. Classic is free forever. Premium is $<%= localised_price %>/year.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="text-center mt-8 mb-4 md:text-xl">
    <%= link_to new_signup_path do %>
      <div class="mt-2 inline-flex font-medium p-4 rounded-xl shadow-sm btn-primary text-xl">Create your free Pagecord account</div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "screenshots" %>

